Seven Stories PressYou offer the Occupy movement as an example of the energy and impact that a group can have.
I set out to interview Chomsky to use in a course I was teaching.
Typically, during a Chomsky interview, these types of comments are simply glossed over.
During the interview, Chomsky and I discussed the importance of public meeting spaces.
In the interview, Chomsky said, “You don’t have Sproul Plaza,” and then went on to discuss how the geography of universities changed specifically to limit meeting space.